I can suggest some potential reasons why certain cities are repeatedly chosen to host the world athletics championships:

1) infrastructure: certain cities have already built or invested in the required infrastructure to host an international sporting event. this includes having a stadium, transportation, and accommodation options that meet international standards;

2) experience: some cities have a history of successfully hosting major international events and have the experience to handle the logistics of hosting such an event as the world athletics championships;

3) location: cities in regions with a strong interest and investment in athletics, or that are geographically located in a favorable position for international travel, may have an advantage in being chosen to host the event;

4) reputation: cities with a positive reputation for their hospitality, safety, and accessibility may be more appealing to the evaluators and decision-makers. 

it is essential to note that these are potential reasons, and various factors influence the decision-making process for choosing host cities for the world athletics championships. the process of selecting a host city can be complex and involve negotiation, incentives, and politics.
